modules.description: This module offers operations for managing string-keyed maps, including insertion, updating, removal, and retrieval of bindings, alongside ordered key traversal, filtering, and transformation. It supports sequence-based manipulation and conversion between maps and lists, enabling efficient handling of structured data with monotonic key relationships. Use cases include configuration management, data processing pipelines, and scenarios requiring ordered key access or incremental map construction.

Parses structured form data from Lwt_stream, extracting POST parameters and file parts. It processes strings and handles streaming input efficiently. Used to extract form data in web applications using cohttp for HTTP requests.

manages string-keyed maps with insertion, update, removal, and retrieval, along with ordered key traversal and transformation. It supports sequence-based operations and conversion between maps and lists, enabling structured data handling. Users can filter, transform, and incrementally build maps, making it suitable for configuration management and data processing. Examples include dynamically updating settings or processing records with ordered keys.
